I have deployed Consul on a Kubernetes Kind cluster and would like to build a lab environment to demonstrate the functionality of Service Router, Service Splitter, and Service Resolver.

The lab should satisfy the following requirements:

Base Applications
static-client and static-server service deployed in the default namespace.
We will use here static-client to access the services.
By default, a request to:
http://static-server should return the response from the static-server application.

Service Router
Route requests based on the URL path:
http://static-server/tea → static-server-tea
http://static-server/coffee → static-server-coffee

Route requests based on an HTTP header or query parameter:
If the request contains header x-debug: 1, route to static-server-header-query-param.
If the request contains query parameter ?x-debug=1, also route to static-server-header-query-param.
curl -s -H "x-debug: 1" static-server.virtual.consul
OR
curl -s static-server.virtual.consul?x-debug=1

Service Splitter
static-server-tea should be split between:
static-server-tea-v1    (10%)
static-server-tea-v2   (90%)
static-server-coffee should be split between:
static-server-coffee-v1    (10%)
static-server-coffee-v2     (90%)
The splitter should demonstrate traffic distribution 

Service Resolver (Failover)
Deploy an identical set of services in a backup namespace.
Configure Consul Service Resolver so that if a service in the default namespace becomes unavailable, traffic automatically fails over to the corresponding service in the backup namespace.

Steps:-
kind create cluster --name=dc1
helm install consul hashicorp/consul --values=values.yaml --version=1.8.15 --debug

cd default_ns_apps (Deploy all applications in default namespace)
execute kubectl apply -f command on all the .yaml files. You may run the below script to achieve this:-
./apply-all.sh

kubectl create ns backup
cd ../backup_ns_apps (Deploy all applications in backup namespace)
execute kubectl apply -f command on all the .yaml files in backup namespace. You may run the below script to achieve this:-
./apply-all.sh

cd ..
kubectl apply -f service-router.yaml
kubectl apply -f service-splitter.yaml
kubectl apply -f service-resolver.yaml
kubectl apply -f proxy-defaults.yaml

