Very Important observation:-

The routing logic defined in service router does not work for api gateway. You have to explicitly define the logic in http routes configuration.
Consul API Gateway is built on the native Kubernetes Gateway API. 
Because the Gateway API uses HTTPRoute as its primary routing engine, the API Gateway completely ignores Consul ServiceRouter resources.
However, service splitter logic works perfectly fine. Refer o/p of line 135 nad 137 above.
The beautiful part of this design is that while the API Gateway ignores ServiceRouters, it still fully respects your ServiceSplitters and ServiceResolvers. 
So your 10/90 traffic splits and backup failovers will continue to work perfectly once the gateway points to the right backend.






